Sentencas: The La0.6Sr0.4Fe03.5-Gd0.1Ce0.9O1.95-delta (LSF-GDC) support with large straight open pores was formed by the phase inversion tape method, and used as a cathode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) comprising GDC electrolyte and Ni-GDC anode.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cells supported on cathodes with large straight open pores and catalyst-decorated surfaces

Sentencas: La0.6Sr0.4CoO3-delta (LSC) nano-particles were deposited deeply inside the cathode using the impregnation method.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cells supported on cathodes with large straight open pores and catalyst-decorated surfaces

Sentencas: The single cell with the LSC-modified cathode exhibited a maximum power density of 726 mW cm(-2) at 750 degrees C, much higher than the one with the un-modified cathode (298 mW cm(-2)).
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cells supported on cathodes with large straight open pores and catalyst-decorated surfaces

Sentencas: The polarization resistance determined with the impedance spectroscopy was 0.025 Omega cm(2) for the former, which was one order of magnitude smaller than that for the latter.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cells supported on cathodes with large straight open pores and catalyst-decorated surfaces

Sentencas: It is concluded that the presence of large straight open pores in the phase inversion-derived cathode allows for easy impregnation of catalytically active nano -particles, enlarging the triple-phase-boundaries for oxygen reduction reaction and hence enhancing the electrochemical performance of the cathode-supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Solid oxide fuel cells supported on cathodes with large straight open pores and catalyst-decorated surfaces
